{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Color\/geometryGroup()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/color\/geometrygroup()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from its parent view."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Color"]]},"metadata":{"platforms":[{"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"iOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"13.0"},{"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"macOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"10.15"},{"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"tvOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"13.0"},{"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"visionOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"1.0"},{"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"watchOS","beta":false,"introducedAt":"6.0"}],"modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI","relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"]}],"symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"geometryGroup"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View"}],"extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE13geometryGroupQryF::SYNTHESIZED::s:15OpenSwiftUICore5ColorV","remoteSource":{"fileName":"RendererEffect.swift","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Render\/RendererEffect\/RendererEffect.swift#L294"},"title":"geometryGroup()","role":"symbol"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"geometryGroup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"By default OpenSwiftUI views push position and size changes down","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"through the view hierarchy, so that only views that draw","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"something (known as leaf views) apply the current animation to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"their frame rectangle. However in some cases this coalescing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"behavior can give undesirable results; inserting a geometry","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"group can correct that. A group acts as a barrier between the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parent view and its subviews, forcing the position and size","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"values to be resolved and animated by the parent, before being","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"passed down to each subview.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example below shows one use of this function: ensuring that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the member views of each row in the stack apply (and animate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as) a single geometric transform from their ancestor view,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"rather than letting the effects of the ancestor views be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"applied separately to each leaf view. If the members of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"ItemView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" may be added and removed at different times the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"group ensures that they stay locked together as animations are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"applied.","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["VStack {","    ForEach(items) { item in","        ItemView(item: item)","            .geometryGroup()","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns: a new view whose geometry is isolated from that of its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parent view."}]}]}],"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui","title":"OpenSwiftUI","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Declare the user interface and behavior for your app on every platform."}]},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/View":{"title":"View","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/view","abstract":[{"text":"A type that represents part of your appâ€™s user interface and provides","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"modifiers that you use to configure views.","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/Color/geometryGroup()":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Color\/geometryGroup()","type":"topic","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/open